comments: White's (CHI) arm extends forward and marginal contact occurs with Towns' (MIN) left arm during the drive.
White (CHI) reaches in and brushes Okogie's (MIN) left arm before Vucevic (CHI) cleanly blocks Okogie's layup attempt.
Brown Jr. (CHI) and Russell (MIN) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Edwards (MIN) makes incidental contact with White's (CHI) right arm as White intercepts the pass.
Reid (MIN) avoids making contact with Vucevic (CHI) and legally contests the dunk attempt.
Brown Jr. (CHI) swipes forward and marginal contact occurs with Russell's (MIN) side as he is passing.
LaVine (CHI) and Okogie (MIN) make incidental body contact with one another as they each attempt to retrieve the loose ball.
Okogie (MIN) delivers body contact to LaVine (CHI) in transition, affecting LaVine's SQBR.
LaVine (CHI) and Okogie (MIN) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
LaVine (CHI) extends his leg as part of his natural shooting motion and marginal contact occurs with Okogie's (MIN) leg during the follow-through.
Okogie (MIN) contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs when LaVine attempts to create the contact with his right leg.
Towns (MIN) firms up in his screening position in White's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Theis' (CHI) left foot is planted on the floor and Theis does not intentionally kick the ball as Russell (MIN) dribbles it off of his foot.
Theis (CHI) and Towns (MIN) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.
Brown Jr. (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Towns' (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
Towns (MIN) is moving alongside LaVine's (CH) path when marginal body contact occurs during LaVine's driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) engages and disengages with Towns (MIN) as Towns moves to set the pick.
Okogie (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball and simultaneous incidental contact with White's (CHI) arm during rebounding.
Towns (MIN) moves A to B and initiates body contact with LaVine (CHI) during the driving shot attempt.

Reid (MIN) and Theis (CHI) come together at the same spot in the lane and marginal contact occurs during rebounding, some of which occurs to Theis' head. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Towns (MIN) and Williams (CHI) engage with one another after the free throw attempt is released and disengage as the ball falls to the opposite side of the lane.
Brown Jr. (CHI) and Russell (MIN) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Theis (CHI) wraps his arm around Towns' (MIN) midsection and initiates contact that affects Towns' SQBR.
Okogie (MIN) and LaVine (CHI) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Okogie (MIN) moves into LaVine's (CHI) space and makes contact to his arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
